<h1>Salma Jafri</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.salmajafri.com/now/">salmajafri.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Karachi

Pakistan
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Host of Content Marketing Tips (#CMtips) web show.  Co-Founder, The Moxie Women.  Team Lead, Google Business Groups for Women, Karachi.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help women entrepreneurs market authentically.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I love marketing but hate the misconceptions around it. People, especially women, seem to think marketing is icky and spammy and they often don't know how to promote themselves. I show them how marketing is all about building relationships and connecting and engaging by being your most authentic self.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
To be good, you need to be badass.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
GirlBoss by Sophia Amoruso
</p>

